Network programmability is really thriving in data center environments, where Nexus devices (large switches) are used.

Netconf was introduced in 2006 by IETF

Restconf in 2017

Cisco aimed to make the Nexus 9K series switches optimal for network programmability

You can interact with them from ACI controller or directly with rest/netconf

Nexus runs on different OS than IOSXE - NXOS is basically linux under the hood - NX-OS

NX-OS Â can run anything linux can (python, ansible, docker) - including the NX-API

Old version NX-API CLI - Using HTTP(s) but not Restful. Every API call made is a POST method

New version NX-API REST -
